The paper deals with error-correcting codes and their relationship with Cayley graphs, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT), discrete structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper's focus on locally testable codes suggests that it may be more closely related to cs.IT and cs.DS, but the use of Cayley graphs and their properties also makes cs.CG and cs.DM possible categories. The paper's emphasis on algebraic structures and graph theory also suggests cs.CC as a possible category.
